OL,3,CVictory for 'local legend' Nelson in
OL,4,Cimmigration battle to remain
OL,6,FITV Granada Reports Content Editor Ian
OL,7,FBarber spoke to Nelson Shardey and his
OL,8,Fson Jacob about successful fight for
OL,9,Fhim to remain in Britain
OL,11,FA man described as a 'local legend' on
OL,12,FMerseyside says he's 'overwhelmed'
OL,13,Fafter the Home Office backed down and
OL,14,Fgranted him leave to remain in the UK
OL,15,Fwhere he's lived for 46 years.
OL,17,FNelson Shardey said: "I feel great and
OL,18,Fhappy that, at last, justice has been
OL,19,Fdone".
